# Mosquitto ACL for the TLS listener (8883) -- see IMPROVEMENTS.md finding A3.
# Only `app` (the phone) and `bridge` (bridge_esp32) authenticate here; the
# loopback listener (1883) stays anonymous/unrestricted for local Pi tooling
# and isn't affected by this file.
#
# bridge_esp32 only ever publishes sensor readings and node-status -- it
# never subscribes to anything (see bridge_esp32.ino). Scoping it to
# publish-only on exactly those topics means a compromised/spoofed bridge
# can't send actuator commands, rewrite rules, or read anything back.
user bridge
topic write greenhouse/+/air/temperature
topic write greenhouse/+/air/humidity
topic write greenhouse/+/soil/moisture
topic write greenhouse/nodes/+/status

# The app is the trusted end-user client: dashboard, actuator control,
# weather rules, notification settings, camera, history -- needs the full
# namespace both ways.
user app
topic readwrite greenhouse/#
